<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <head>
        <link href="../../../../Stylesheets/Shared/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">(default) </span>The most appropriate movie format is used, based on the Flare output type that you generate. If you build a <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.HTMLHelp" />, <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp" />, <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.HTML5" />, or <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp Plus" /> target, the movie uses the <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.HTML5" /> movie format. If you want to override these settings, select one of the specific movie types below.</li>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">MadCap Movie Player </span>The movie is generated in MMF and displays in the MadCap Movie Viewer. </li>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">
                    <MadCap:keyword term="Adobe Flash" />Adobe Flash </span>The movie is generated in a Flash SWF file.</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Adobe Flash (Embed) </span>The movie is generated in a Flash SWF file and is embedded in your output.</li>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">
                    <MadCap:keyword term="Microsoft Silverlight" />Microsoft Silverlight </span>The movie is generated in the Microsoft Silverlight format.</li>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">
                    <MadCap:keyword term="HTML5:movie format;Movies:HTML5" />HTML5 </span>The movie is generated in the HTML5 movie format.</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">HTML5 (Embed) </span>The movie is generated in the HTML5 movie format and is embedded in your output.</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>